"title": "6629: conversion, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6629",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture gives examples of individuals and peoples who have turned to God in conversion.</p>\n<h2>Examples of conversion in the OT</h2>\n<h3>Peoples who turned to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:22\">ISA 19:22</a> <em>Egypt</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:5-Jonah3:10\">JON 3:5–3:10</a> <em>Nineveh</em></p>\n<h2>Individuals who turned to God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:15\">2KI 5:15</a> <em>Naaman</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:12-2Chr33:13\">2CH 33:12–33:13</a> <em>Manasseh</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:34-Dan4:37\">DAN 4:34–4:37</a> <em>Nebuchadnezzar</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:16\">JON 1:16</a> <em>sailors on board ship with Jonah</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of conversion in the NT</h2>\n<h3>Examples of people in general</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:42\">JHN 4:42</a> <em>people of Sychar</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:41\">ACT 2:41</a> <em>3,000 people on the day of Pentecost</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:12\">ACT 8:12</a> <em>Samaritans</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:35\">ACT 9:35</a> <em>people of Lydda and Sharon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:3\">ACT 15:3</a> <em>Gentile converts</em></p>\n<h3>Examples of individual converts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:18\">LUK 15:18</a> <em>the prodigal son</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8-Luke19:9\">LUK 19:8–19:9</a> <em>Zacchaeus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:35-Acts8:38\">ACT 8:35–8:38</a> <em>the Ethiopian eunuch</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:3-Acts9:18\">ACT 9:3–9:18</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:6-Acts22:11\">ACT 22:6–22:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:12-Acts26:18\">ACT 26:12–26:18</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:44-Acts10:48\">ACT 10:44–10:48</a> <em>Cornelius</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:12\">ACT 13:12</a> <em>the proconsul, Sergius Paulus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:14-Acts16:15\">ACT 16:14–16:15</a> <em>Lydia</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:29-Acts16:34\">ACT 16:29–16:34</a> <em>the Philippian jailer</em></p>\n<h2>The prophetic vision of the future conversion of Israel and the nations</h2>\n<h3>Israel's turning back to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:5\">HOS 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:4-Jer50:5\">JER 50:4–50:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:10-Hos11:11\">HOS 11:10–11:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:26\">ROM 11:26</a></p>\n<h3>The conversion of the nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:19\">JER 16:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:27-Ps22:28\">PSA 22:27–22:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:3\">ISA 2:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:2\">MIC 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:16\">ZEC 14:16</a></p>",
